# Nonoise Media - Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js (App Router)
- React
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion (for all complex animations)
- Lucide React (for icons)

## Design System & Aesthetic
- Vibe: Premium, cinematic, minimalist, dark-mode default.
- Typography: Use the established ultra-condensed fonts for headings and clean sans-serif for body. Keep line-heights tight (`leading-none` or `leading-tight`) for stacked text.
- Spacing: Embrace negative space. Do not clutter the UI.
- Buttons: Avoid standard web buttons. Use the "highlighted text" style with tight padding.
- Animations: Use Framer Motion with spring physics (e.g., `stiffness: 300, damping: 20`) for fluid, organic micro-interactions. Avoid rigid, linear CSS transitions.

## Coding Standards
- Write clean, modular, functional React components.
- Keep client-side logic (hooks, state, Framer Motion) in files marked with `"use client"`.
- When handling video, strictly use standard HTML5 `<video>` tags and `useRef` hooks to manage playback state, time updates, and muting. Do NOT restart the video on state changes unless explicitly requested.
- Prioritize single-file components for simple layouts, but extract complex SVG animations (like the hamburger menu) into their own components.